23/06/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Albanian Prime Minister Sali Berisha addressed the European Parliament's (EP) Foreign Affairs Committee on Thursday (22 June) in Brussels.
Berisha briefed the EP members on his country's reform process, highlighting the fight against organised crime, illegal trafficking and corruption.
The prime minister appealed for increased EU support for infrastructure improvement and for the realisation of Transport Corridor VIII project -- which, according to Berisha, is of high importance for the future economic achievements.
While in Brussels, Berisha also met with the president of the Belgian Senate, Anne-Marie Lizin.
(Albanian News - 23/06/06)
